    "title": "Clan violence in Sool region displaces hundreds, destroys homes and businesses",
    "original_title": "Clan conflict in Sool destroys family livelihoods and forces hundreds to flee",
    "slug": "clan-violence-in-sool-region-displaces-hundreds-destroys-homes-and-businesses",
    "summary": "Clashes in Madah-lagu Hoor, Sool region, in early June have displaced hundreds of families and destroyed livelihoods, including a local café owner's shop and home. The conflict underscores ongoing insecurity in the region affecting Somali communities.",
    "content": "In early June, violent clan clashes erupted in the settlement of Madah-lagu Hoor, located in Somalia's Sool region, causing widespread displacement and destruction. Hundreds of families have been forced to flee their homes as their properties and sources of income were burned down or destroyed.\n\nAmong those affected is Sahra Faah Ali, a local woman who ran a small café in Madah-lagu. She used to prepare and sell meals and groceries, earning between six and ten dollars daily. That income supported her family's food, water, children's education, and other household costs. Her café, along with her two-room corrugated iron home, kitchen, and latrine, were all consumed by fire during the clashes. Additionally, six of her goats were lost.\n\nThe conflict adds to the history of clan tensions in the Sool region, which has seen periodic violence over land and resources. Madah-lagu Hoor, a rural area, is now partly deserted as many residents seek safety elsewhere. The displacement places additional strain on already limited resources in host communities.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, this event highlights the fragility of peace in their homeland and the direct impact on families' economic stability. Many diaspora members support relatives in Somalia through remittances, which are now harder to sustain when livelihoods are destroyed. The situation also underscores the need for conflict resolution and humanitarian aid to prevent further suffering.\n\nRead the original report from Radio Ergo here: https://radioergo.org/en/2026/07/clan-conflict-in-sool-destroys-family-livelihoods-and-forces-hundreds-to-flee/",
    "source": "radioergo.org",
