    "original_title": "Wasiirka Gaashaandhigga iyo Taliyaha Ciidanka Xoogga Dalka oo kormeeray Dugsiga Tababarka Ciidanka ee Qorilow",
    "slug": "somali-defense-minister-and-army-chief-inspect-qorilow-military-training-base",
    "summary": "Somalia’s Defense Minister Ahmed Moalim Fiqi and Army Chief General Ibrahim Mohamed Mohamud visited the Qorilow training base in Middle Shabelle region, urging troops to enhance their training quality and readiness for security operations.",
    "content": "Somalia’s Defense Minister Ahmed Moalim Fiqi, accompanied by the Chief of the Somali National Army, General Ibrahim Mohamed Mohamud, conducted an inspection visit to the Qorilow Military Training Base in the Middle Shabelle region on Wednesday. The tour aimed to assess the ongoing training programs and the overall readiness of the forces stationed there.\n\nDuring the visit, Minister Fiqi addressed the troops, emphasizing the importance of discipline, professionalism, and dedication in their training. He called on the soldiers to double their efforts and maintain high standards as they prepare for future security missions. The minister also reiterated the federal government’s commitment to strengthening the country’s defense capabilities.\n\nThe Qorilow base serves as a key training facility for Somali forces, including those integrated from regional states. The inspection reflects the government’s focus on building a unified and effective national army capable of taking over security responsibilities from international partners.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, this visit signals progress in the reconstruction of national security institutions. Many in the diaspora have supported state-building efforts through remittances and advocacy. A professional and well-trained army is seen as essential for long-term stability, which in turn encourages investment and family reunification.\n\nRead the original report from Goobjoog here: https://goobjoog.com/2026/07/08/wasiirka-gaashaandhigga-iyo-taliyaha-ciidanka-xoogga-dalka-oo-kormeeray-dugsiga-tababarka-ciidanka-ee-qorilow/",
